e essential components of the broader treatment strategy. The relationship between 脱毒治疗 and 预防复吸 highlights the need for a comprehensive approach that addresses both the physical and psychological aspects of addiction [Data: Entities (843), Relationships (999)].\n\n## 戒毒者 as the focus of rehabilitation efforts\n\n戒毒者 (Rehabilitated Individuals) are the primary focus of the community's efforts, particularly in the context of 社会心理康复. These individuals have undergone drug rehabilitation and are in the process of reintegrating into society. The relationship between 社会心理康复 and 戒毒者 emphasizes the importance of providing ongoing support to ensure successful recovery and reduce the risk of relapse [Data: Entities (863), Relationships (1024)].\n\n## Interconnectedness of treatment components\n\nThe community's entities are highly interconnected, with each playing a crucial role in the overall treatment and rehabilitation process. 社会心理康复, 预防复吸, 脱毒治疗, and 戒毒者 are all part of a broader strategy to address opioid addiction and support recovery. The relationships between these entities highlight the need for a comprehensive and integrated approach to treatment, addressing both the immediate and long-term needs of individuals struggling with addiction [Data: Relationships (1023, 1001, 1024, 999)].", "# Psychological Care and Nurse-Patient Relationship\n\nThe community focuses on psychological care in psychiatric nursing, emphasizing the importance of the nurse-patient relationship. Psychological care is tailored to address the diverse psychological reactions of psychiatric patients, while a good nurse-patient relationship is foundational for effective psychological care.\n\n## Psychological care as a core component\n\nPsychological care is a central entity in this community, focusing on addressing the varied psychological reactions of psychiatric patients. This care is essential for helping patients resolve their psychological issues and promoting their recovery. The relationship 